        "theory": "## C Basics\nC is a compiled language. You must compile the code before running it. We use `printf` from `<stdio.h>` for output.\n```c\n#include <stdio.h>\nint main() {\n    printf(\"Hello, World!\\n\");\n    return 0;\n}\n```",
        "instructions": "## Task: Hello C\nWrite a basic C program that prints `'Hello C'` followed by a newline.",
