        "theory": "## Custom Hooks\nExtract component logic into reusable functions starting with 'use'.\n```jsx\nfunction useWindowWidth() {\n  const [width, setWidth] = useState(window.innerWidth);\n  // ...\n  return width;\n}\n```",
        "instructions": "## Task: useToggle Hook\nCreate a custom hook `useToggle` that manages a boolean state and returns `[value, toggleFunction]`.",
        "starterCode": "import { useState } from 'react';\n\nfunction ___useToggle(initial) {\n  const [val, setVal] = useState(initial);\n  const toggle = () => setVal(!val);\n  return ___, ___;\n}",
        "solution": "import { useState } from 'react';\nfunction useToggle(initial) {\n  const [val, setVal] = useState(initial);\n  const toggle = () => setVal(!val);\n  return [val, toggle];\n}",
        "hint": "useToggle and return [val, toggle]",
